{
  "text": "Remark. Evolution groups and their generators given by conditions of the type of (4.5) (or (4.13)) were introduced in [CITATION_1] , where the group U (t) is specified by the condition U (t)\u2126 0 = \u2126 0 . where \u2126 0 is the unperturbed vector (\"vacuum\") introduced in (2.37) above. However, an analysis of the operator K (see Sections 6 and 7) defined this way requires, instead of Condition (A), the condition obtained from Condition (A) by replacing the weight e \u03b4\u03b2j |u|/2 by e \u03b2j|u|/2 (and correpondingly, e (\u03b2\u2212\u03b2j)|k| has to be replaced by e \u03b2j|k| in (4.1)). This leads to an additional restriction on the temperatures of the form min",
